item.dc:creator: @defyboy defyboy
item.description:
@defyboy wrote:

or this:

[code]// Runescape Pack200 Converter
// ©2006 Troy Osborne - defyboy@gmail.com

import java.io.;
import java.util.jar.Pack200;
import java.util.jar.Pack200.;
import java.util.jar.JarOutputStream;
import java.util.zip.GZIPInputStream;

public class RSUnpacker
{
public static final void main(String args[]) {
if(args.length < 2){
System.out.println(“Usage: RSUnpacker [input] [output]”);
System.out.println(“Eg: RSUnpacker runescape.pack200 runescape.jar”);
System.exit(2);
}
byte input[] = readfile(args[0]);
byte file[] = new byte[input.length + 2];
file[0] = 31;
file[1] = -117;
System.arraycopy(input, 0, file, 2, input.length);
try{
FileOutputStream fostream = new FileOutputStream(args[1]);
JarOutputStream jostream = new JarOutputStream(fostream);
Unpacker unpacker = Pack200.newUnpacker();
unpacker.unpack(new GZIPInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(file)), jostream);
jostream.close();
System.out.println("Extracted " + args[0] + " to: " + args[1]);
} catch (IOException ioe) {
ioe.printStackTrace();
}
}

public static final byte[] readfile(String s) {
	try {
		File file = new File(s);
		if(!file.exists()) {
			return null;
		}
		else {
			int i = (int)file.length();
			byte abyte0[] = new byte[i];
			DataInputStream datainputstream = new DataInputStream(new BufferedInputStream(new FileInputStream(s)));
			datainputstream.readFully(abyte0, 0, i);
			datainputstream.close();
			return abyte0;
		}
    }
	catch(Throwable _ex) {
		_ex.printStackTrace();
	}
	return null;
}

}
[/code]
